In the last post, we looked at Sachin's Test Performances. And as promised, I will create some stats on ODI performances of Sachin, Lara and Ponting. We will keep this limited to comparing performances of all three.I will create two stats comparing their performances. One how they played against each country and the other on how they performed over yearsduring their respective careers.

<strong>Performances Against Opponents</strong>

Created a heatmap, showing their average performances against each country. This is an interactive graph that you can explore by moving your mouse over it.

[cf]bycountries[/cf]

Key Insights: Lara played better against Sri Lanka and new Zealand compared to other opponents. Ricky ponting is better against their arch rival England and New Zealand. Whereas Sachin is clearly best against Australia and West Indies.

Visibly, Lara is comparatively weak against England and India, Ponting against Pakistan and West Indies, where as Sachin is weak against South Africa.

<strong>How they performed over time in their careers?</strong>

[cf]bytime[/cf]

Clearly, Sachin had played longer then Lara and Ponting. His career spanned from 1990 to 2012. He had crossed 1500/year mark twice, where asthe others did not manage it. Lara managed only once to cross 1000 mark in a year, whereas Sachin managed that feat 6 times and Ponting 5 times.

Lara peaked during early in his career, while Ponting seems to have peaked during later part of his career. Sachin had peaked manytimes after few bad periods.

That's all from me now. Please share your thoughts and opinions.
